        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 8:27PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 827 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 16 miles southwest of Absarokee to 6
miles southwest of Red Lodge, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, along with brief moderate rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Red Lodge, Bearcreek, Luther, Roscoe, Fishtail, Fox, Dean, Washoe,
Roberts and Nye.

As these storms move off the foothills, gusty crosswinds could
impact travel on US-212 from Red Lodge to Roberts, and Highway 78
from Red lodge to Roscoe.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
